The paper deals with coding theory, specifically skew cyclic codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves algebraic structures and properties of rings, which falls under the category of computational geometry (cs.GT). Additionally, the paper presents an encoding and decoding algorithm, which is a topic in cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also involves the study of minimal spanning sets, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper provides examples of codes with good parameters, which is a topic in machine learning and pattern recognition (cs.SI).
